The "psdraft" command is a PostScript filter which will print the
word "DRAFT" and the current date diagonally across each page in a
light grey shading.  This provides a means for marking unofficial
copies of a document or memo in a very obvious way.

12/9/91 update:
Options have been added to allow the user to change the word "DRAFT"
and/or the current date from their default printed values.

4/7/92 update:
Additional PostScript formats (e.g. FrameMaker) are now recognized.

4/10/92 update:
Added compatibility with new nawk.

3/7/94 update:
Added an option to control the grey level of the underlying text.
Added compatibility for DWB 3.4 and postprint.
